The paper deals with communication networks and their performance, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT). The use of analog network coding and layered relay networks suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses approximation schemes and performance bounds, which are common topics in the field of theoretical computer science (cs.SI). The use of Gaussian diamond networks and symmetric layered networks suggests a focus on multimedia and signal processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of network performance, which is a common topic in the field of data science (cs.DS).
